## OUTCOME DISTRIBUTION (from 363 filtered backtest trades — OLD LADDER 1.5/2.5/4.0R)
**NOTE**: These probabilities are from the old TP ladder. The new 1.0/2.0/3.5R ladder will shift outcomes:
- TP1 at 1.0R will hit MORE often (closer target) → fewer losses, more partial wins
- TP3 at 3.5R will hit LESS often → fewer full winners but they're still profitable
- Net effect: higher win rate, lower average R per win — needs live data to calibrate

Use these as APPROXIMATE probabilities until new ladder has 100+ resolved signals:
- **47%** of trades: -1.0R (LOSS — hit stop loss) — likely LOWER with tighter TP1
- **3%** of trades: 0R (EXPIRED — no TP, no SL within 48h)
- **20%** of trades: +1.0R (WIN_PARTIAL — hit TP1 only) — likely HIGHER with closer target
- **17%** of trades: +2.0R (WIN_PARTIAL — hit TP1+TP2)
- **13%** of trades: +3.5R (WIN_FULL — hit TP1→TP2→TP3) — likely LOWER

## POSITION SIZING
- **Risk per trade**: 4% of current account equity (compounded)
- **Burst dampener**: >5 signals/hour → risk drops to 2%
- **Burst exposure cap**: Max 25% of equity per burst hour (at 4% = max 6 trades)
- **Portfolio manager burst cap**: Max 3 new positions per burst (correlation-aware)
- **Max concurrent positions**: 10 (exec engine enforced)
- **Portfolio heat limit**: 80% of account equity

## SIGNAL CLUSTERING (CRITICAL)
Signals arrive in correlated bursts, NOT independently:
- Burst days: 10-30 signals within 1-3 hours (correlated altcoin squeezes)
- Quiet periods: 0-2 signals per day for 3-7 days
- Portfolio manager now caps at 3 per burst AND rejects correlated signals
- Within a burst: ~40% bad (70% loss rate), ~60% good (70% win rate)

**LIVE VALIDATION**: Day 1 burst (7 trades, 8% risk) had 100% loss rate. Day 3 burst (April 2): 7 STRICT signals, ALL hit SL. Burst correlation is severe and real.

## KILL SWITCH
- 30% drawdown from weekly HWM: system pauses
- 50% drawdown from peak: system halts, all positions closed
- Any simulation path hitting 50% DD from peak is TERMINATED

